        <div class="nd-panel active" data-section="intro">
            <div class="nd-panel-header">
                <span class="nd-panel-tag">Overview</span>
                <h2>Divisions</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="comp-body">

                <h3>Sugar, Cogen &amp; Bio-chemicals Business</h3>
                <p>For over seventy years, TKIL Industries has been a pioneer in providing innovative, turnkey solutions to the sugar industry, including sugar refineries and cogen plants. With a growing commitment to sustainability, TKIL Industries recently ventured into the bio-chemicals sector, encompassing distilleries, compressed bio-gas plants, and their associated derivatives. This legacy of excellence has firmly established us as a trusted leader in delivering sustainable energy solutions to the global sugar, cogen, and bio-chemicals industries.</p>

                <h3>Mining, Material Handling and BOP Business</h3>
                <p>TKIL Industries is a technologically driven engineering powerhouse, with exceptional contributions in the areas of Mining, Bulk Material Handling and Comminution (Crushing and Grinding) System and Equipment. Powered by world class technology, TKIL Industries has proven itself as the most reliable and versatile solution provider in this field, for everything from concept to commissioning. TKIL Industries provides end-to-end solutions for core sectors such as mining, power, ports, steel and minerals.</p>

                <h3>Cement Plants and Equipment Business</h3>
                <p>TKIL Industries, one of the world's leading cement and mining technology companies, has been manufacturing, supplying, installing and commissioning modern, state-of-art and most efficient integrated cement plants of capacities ranging between 650 to 10000 tpd, as well as split location grinding units in India and overseas for more than 35 years.</p>
                <p>TKIL Industries also provides comprehensive service activities for complete cement production line, individual products, plant upgrades and conversions, and undertakes O&amp;M activities.</p>
                <p>TKIL Industries plants are in operation across the length and breadth of India, running at more than their rated capacities, and are distinct on account of their sustained efficiency and output levels.</p>

                <h3>Energy Business (Boiler and Power Plants)</h3>
                <p>TKIL Industries has long established itself in the field of design, manufacture, supply, installation and commissioning of a wide range of steam and power generation plants for a host of industrial applications.</p>
                <p>Leveraging its leadership position in Circulating Fluidized Combustion Bed Boilers, the company has expanded its range of offerings to provide complete power plants on EPC basis.</p>
                <p>A comprehensive range of steam generating plants including solid fuel fired boilers (coal, lignite, pet coke, bagasse, biomass and others), waste heat recovery boilers and oil/gas fired boilers form the backbone of these power plants. These steam generating plants are available on standalone basis and are the industry benchmark for their multifuel capability, high efficiency, reliability and environment friendliness.</p>

                <h3>Service Business</h3>
                <p>360° service program supports our customer throughout the life cycle of their assets i.e. spare parts supply, O&amp;M service and field service ensure that the assets are functional and producing required results throughout its operations life. For assets closing to the end of their life cycle, we offer revamps and rejuvenation service to further increase the operating life with guaranteed output and safety. With our service portfolio, we are always with our customers and are helping them in achieving their business goals.</p>

                <h3>Green Hydrogen Business</h3>
                <p>TKIL Industries is at the forefront of India's green energy transition with its foray into the green hydrogen sector. Through a strategic partnership with SoHHytec SA, based in Lausanne, Switzerland, whose novel green hydrogen technology operates directly sun to hydrogen production with a &gt;2x solar to hydrogen efficiency while 1/3rd land use compared with a solar PV+Electrolyser combination unit. SoHHytec is a cutting-edge innovator and solutions provider in the green hydrogen field using its proprietary artificial photosynthesis (photo-electrolysis) technology. We aim to drive the production of clean, renewable hydrogen using solar and wind power. Green hydrogen is set to play a pivotal role in decarbonizing key industries, including fertilizers, oil and gas, steel, cement, and mobility.</p>
                <p>By aligning with India's National Hydrogen Mission, we are committed to becoming a leader in the green hydrogen revolution, contributing to the nation's energy security and supporting its path to net-zero emissions. Our innovative solutions focus on sustainability, energy efficiency, and scalability, ensuring that the transition to green hydrogen benefits both industry and the environment.</p>
                <p>At TKIL Industries, we are committed to unlocking the full potential of green hydrogen as a clean energy source for a sustainable tomorrow.</p>

                <h3>Battery and Energy Storage Business</h3>
                <p>TKIL Industries, a distinguished leader in industrial engineering and manufacturing, has entered into an exclusive strategic agreement with Germany's HOPPECKE Batterie Systeme GmbH — Europe's preeminent industrial battery systems manufacturer. This collaboration is dedicated to delivering advanced, sustainable Railway Battery Systems to support the rapid expansion of India's rail transportation sector.</p>

