            <div class="comp-body">

                <p>As the global energy landscape undergoes rapid transformation, industries face an imperative to reduce reliance on fossil fuels and adopt cleaner, more sustainable solutions. TKIL Industries Pvt. Ltd. recognizes this critical juncture as an opportunity to lead and enable the transition toward green energy systems that not only meet today's demands but also prepare industries for a sustainable future. By integrating innovative technologies, fostering strategic partnerships, and leveraging our expertise in EPC solutions, we are committed to helping industries achieve energy independence, reduce carbon footprints, and align with international climate goals. Our green hydrogen initiative symbolizes this commitment, offering industries a viable pathway to a cleaner and greener tomorrow.</p>

                <p><strong>Partnership with SoHHytec:</strong> To revolutionize the energy transition, TKIL Industries has forged a strategic partnership with SoHHytec, a global innovator in green hydrogen technology. This collaboration combines TKIL's legacy of engineering excellence with SoHHytec's state-of-the-art advancements in artificial photosynthesis, ensuring groundbreaking solutions for industries transitioning to renewable energy. Together, we aim to:</p>

                <ul class="div-list">
                    <li><strong>Decarbonize Industries:</strong> Provide sustainable, zero-carbon energy solutions.</li>
                    <li><strong>Ensure Energy Independence:</strong> Empower industries to generate energy on-site, minimizing reliance on external sources.</li>
                    <li><strong>Promote Scalable Solutions:</strong> Deliver modular systems that grow alongside industry needs.</li>
                </ul>

                <p><strong>About SoHHytec:</strong> SoHHytec is at the forefront of green hydrogen innovation, transforming how energy is produced and consumed. Their proprietary Arb system is a technological marvel designed to address the challenges of traditional energy sources while opening up new possibilities for decentralized and efficient energy production.</p>

                <h3>Key Features of SoHHytec:</h3>

                <ol class="div-list gh-feature-list">
                    <li>
                        <strong>ARB System Innovation:</strong>
                        <ul class="div-list gh-sublist">
                            <li>A modular, scalable solution capable of producing hydrogen, oxygen, and heat simultaneously.</li>
                            <li>Powered solely by sunlight and water, ensuring a 100% renewable process.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Decades of Research Excellence:</strong>
                        <ul class="div-list gh-sublist">
                            <li>Technology rooted in more than 10 years of R&amp;D conducted at the prestigious Swiss Federal Institute of Technology (EPFL) in Lausanne, Switzerland.</li>
                            <li>World-record efficiency in solar-to-hydrogen conversion, making it a leader in the renewable energy space.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Decentralization Focus:</strong>
                        <ul class="div-list gh-sublist">
                            <li>Enables on-site energy generation, eliminating the high costs of hydrogen transportation.</li>
                            <li>Ideal for industries and regions aiming for energy independence and sustainability.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>High Efficiency and Sustainability:</strong>
                        <ul class="div-list gh-sublist">
                            <li>Arb systems achieve a total efficiency of ~80%, with significant solar-to-hydrogen (~25%) and solar-to-electricity (~36%) conversion rates.</li>
                            <li>Medical-grade oxygen and useful heat are valuable by-products, adding economic and functional benefits for industrial operations.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Scalability for Any Industry:</strong>
                        <ul class="div-list gh-sublist">
                            <li>Whether for small-scale operations or large industrial setups, SoHHytec's technology is adaptable and designed for seamless expansion.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ol>

                <h3>Product Offering Range:</h3>

