            <div class="comp-body">

                <p>TKIL Industries, a distinguished leader in industrial engineering and manufacturing, has entered into an exclusive strategic agreement with Germany's HOPPECKE Batterie Systeme GmbH – Europe's preeminent industrial battery systems manufacturer. This collaboration is dedicated to delivering advanced, sustainable Railway Battery Systems to support the rapid expansion of India's rail transportation sector.</p>

                <h3>Partnership Highlights</h3>
                <ul class="div-list">
                    <li><strong>Exclusive Collaboration:</strong> TKIL Industries is the exclusive supplier of HOPPECKE's Railway Battery Systems within the Indian rail market.</li>
                    <li><strong>Joint Development:</strong> Both entities will jointly design, manufacture, and integrate nickel-cadmium (NiCd) battery systems, inclusive of cells, containers, and accessories, across a spectrum of rail applications such as metros, regional trains, and locomotives.</li>
                    <li><strong>Initial Project:</strong> The first joint initiative under this partnership is scheduled for deployment in 2025.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Strategic Significance</h3>
                <ul class="div-list">
                    <li>India aims to double its electric locomotive capacity by 2030.</li>
                    <li>The number of operational metro cities is projected to rise from 23 in FY25 to 31 by FY30, driving demand for over 20,000 electric locomotives.</li>
                    <li>Approximately 900 kilometres of metro rail projects are underway, supported by investments exceeding INR 600 crore.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Combined Expertise</h3>
                <ul class="div-list">
                    <li><strong>TKIL Industries:</strong> Renowned for its engineering excellence, manufacturing capabilities, and comprehensive project management in large-scale industrial ventures.</li>
                    <li><strong>HOPPECKE Batterie Systeme GmbH:</strong> A global leader with over 95 years of expertise in industrial energy storage and railway battery technologies.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Technology and Product Portfolio</h3>
                <ul class="div-list">
                    <li><strong>Nickel-Cadmium (NiCd) Railway Battery Systems:</strong> Exclusively supplied through this collaboration.</li>
                    <li><strong>Battery Energy Storage Systems (BESS):</strong> Currently under joint development for next-generation rail applications.</li>
                    <li><strong>Core Offerings:</strong> Advanced battery systems tailored to meet the specific demands of metro and railway transport.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>About HOPPECKE Batterie Systeme GmbH</h3>
                <p>Established in 1927 and headquartered in Brilon, Germany, HOPPECKE is the largest independent manufacturer of industrial battery systems in Europe. With a global presence comprising 22 subsidiaries and a workforce exceeding 2,000 employees, the company records annual revenues surpassing €600 million. HOPPECKE's solutions enable emission-free mobility for industrial vehicles and rail applications and provide reliable energy storage for renewable energy sources. In 2025, HOPPECKE was recognized as one of the top 500 global market leaders in railway battery technology.</p>

